@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

HL-Plugin is an Amiga port of the famous Hotline Client for Mac and Windows.
It is in the same category as AmiComSys, i.e. an online chat program.

It runs as an plugin inside AmiComSys 2.4+.

The Hotline system is made up of:
* The Hotline Client - the client that connects to the server
* The Hotline Server - the server to connect to
* The Hotline Tracker - keeps track of the servers that are available

For more information visit:

http://www.hotspringsinc.com
http://www.vivahx.com


@endnode
@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

@{b}Requirements @{ub}

HL-Plugin requires:
* AmiComSys 2.4+ (http://www.parting.nu/AmiComSys/)
* 68020+ CPU
* AmigaOS 3.0+
* Textinput.mcc (ftp://ftp.vapor.com/misc/Textinput_xx_xx.lzx)
* amarquee.library v.52+ (included with AmiComSys)
* NListtree.mcc 18.5+ (Aminet: dev/mui/MCC_NListtree.lha)
* NList.mcc 19.98+ (Aminet: dev/mui/MCC_NList0_90.lha)


@endnode
@node INSTALLATION "Installation"

@{b}Installation@{ub}

Use the installer program.

The HL Plugin package is divided into to parts:
* The main part
* The image icons (which is shown to the left of the users if available)

@endnode

@node THEGUI "The GUI"

@{b}The GUI@{ub}

You may switch to the HL Plugin GUI by choosing HL Plugin in the AmiComSys Plugin selection bar, by picking the "View/Switch to plugin/HL PLUGIN" or the HL PLUGIN menuitems.

The contact list takes up the most part of the window. Here all the users that are connected to the server is shown. To the left of their nick name there is an icon.

Below the list there is a toolbar:

@{b}Servers@{ub}
Here you may add Hotline servers and trackers.
Examples of trackers are tracked.group.org and hltracker.com.
An example of a server is hlserver.com.

@{b}Connect/Disconnect@{ub}
Connect or disconnect to the server set in the settings.

@{b}Agree@{ub}
Show the agreement if any. Here you may also agree to it, but you don't have to.

@{b}Files@{ub}
Opens the Files window. Here you may download files from the server or upload. Usually you don't have rights to download from or upload to server. Read the News or the Agreement to find out what to do to get a username on the server with more rights.
Files are downloaded to the AMICOMSYS:plugins/HL_Downloads directory.
You may cancel a download by open the Task window and select the download. Then pick the break command from the context menu. You may also click the close gadget of the transfer window.

@{b}News@{ub}
Opens the News window. Depending on the server version, this is a message window or another window with threaded news items.
If the server version is 1.5 they are threaded and you may also post.

@{b}PChat@{ub}
Opens a personal chat session with the selected user.

@{b}Chat@{ub}
Opens the public chat window.

@{b}UserI@{ub}
Shows info about the selected user, if you have the rights.

@{b}Mess@{ub}
Opens the normal AmiComSys message window and let you send a message to the selected user.

HL Plugin uses the AmiComSys Message History to save all messages.
To Ignore users use the Ignore List (View/Ignore users menu) in AmiComSys.
For the Message windows the normal AmiComSys ones are used.


@endnode
@node THESETTINGS "The settings"

@{b}The settings @{ub}

Pick the Settings/HL Plugin Settings menu item to open the settings window.

@{fg fill}Network settings@{fg text}
@{b}Login @{ub}
The login name used to logon to the server, usually 'guest'.

@{b}Password@{ub}
The password used to logon to the server. Usually empty.

@{b}Nickname@{ub}
The nick name you want to use

@{b}Icon@{ub}
The number of the icon you want to show to the left of you nick name in the list.
Take a look inside the AMICOMSYS:plugins/HL_Images to find a number you want to use. There are many icons in this directory so it may take a while to list it.

@{b}Servername@{ub}
The server to connect to. An example is hlserver.com

@{fg fill}File transfer settings@{fg text}
Don't queue download/uploads. By default the donwloads and uploads are queued. The policy of most servers is that you have to queue your downloads.



@endnode
@node HISTORY "History"

@{b}History@{ub}

@{fg fill}01.06.2003 version 1.2@{fg text}
NEW: Enhanced the error handling for the file transfer.
BUGFIX: Fixed a race condition with the file transfer queue.
BUGFIX: File resume implemented (working with hxd, not HL Server).
NEW: Added "Kick selected user" and "bann selected user" to the Action menu.
NEW: Added "Delete"(file) and "MakeDir" to the Files window.
BUGFIX: Upload didn't work with all servers and files.
BUGFIX: The close button of a transfer window did't work. It just closed the user list connection.
BUGFIX: Forgot to close the transfer window when you got a "file already exists" error.
BUGFIX: Transfers the info written in the Bookmarks section in the "HL Plugin Servers" window when the
connect button is pressed or when the window is closed. Before the old info was sent to the server when you
had forgotten to press return in the text boxes you had modified.
BUGFIX: There was an error with the bookmark save routine (possible enforcer hit).
NEW: A connection to a server, tracker or file server will now not block HL Plugin while
it is connecting. It's now possible to cancel a connection while it is connecting.
NEW: After a file download has finished the program now ask if you want to display it.

@{fg fill}02.12.2001 version 1.0@{fg text}
Updated .guide and installer.
The installer will now automatically configure AmiComSys to start the HL PLUGIN.

@{fg fill}25.11.2001 version 1.0@{fg text}
First version released

@endnode


